[normal]Our Evidence[bold]What is LARA?[bold]Financial benefits to the rural community[bold]Disinformation about our activities[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Recreational motoring on unsealed roads and byways is an emotive and complex issue. Some people think that motor vehicles should simply be banned from unsealed roads and nothing is easily going to change that view, but there is increasingly a ‘middle ground’ approach from highway authorities, which seeks to apply a considered ‘least r
[normal]e
[normal]strictive approach’ philosophy to traffic management on our minor highways.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]LARA believes that consensus management of motor traffic on unsealed roads, appr
[normal]o
[normal]priate to the circumstances in each case, together with sufficient maintenance and a r
[normal]e
[normal]alistic expectation of what a byway should be like, is the way ahead.
